Wonderful food! My husband and I were looking for a place to grab lunch on a Saturday and this place did not disappoint. I had a big craving for some good tacos and stopped in as we were passing by. Got a seat right away, ordered our food with a very friendly and welcoming young lady, and received everything right away. My husband got the pastor quesadillas and i got the pork tacos. I now have one happy husband and one happy belly!! This is a great place to grab some tasty food!!!

Update 11/19 They've added more seating. I still love the food!! Great little hole in the wall Mexican restaurant. No frills. This is definitely more of a carry out spot compared to a date spot but they have a great selection of Mexican drinks and icecreams. The menu is limited but authentic.

REAL authentic Mexican food. If your looking for some great Mexican food this is a little hidden gem. The menu is written in Spanish on one side and English on the other side. I’ve tried the tacos and burritos which were amazing and also didn’t cost a fortune. They have this sauce for the tacos that is so good I love the spice in it. If you’re looking for some REAL authentic Mexican food in Covington you’ve got to try this place.

Family owned, very friendly and authentic fare. If you're looking for snazzy decor or Mexican food smothered in cheese this isn't the place for you. I eat here all the time and it's always really good.

Yes, it's small. No, its not fancy. But oh man - The food is fantastic! I highly recommend the bistek (beefsteak) tacos. A little queso fresco, onion, cilantro, and some fresh lime juice - MUY DELICIOSO!!  Very authentic, and they even have some original family recipes. The staff is also wonderful, and knowing a little bit of Spanish goes a long way.  Sure the place could look a little nicer, but the food gets 5/5 stars. JUST FYI, THIS IS CASH ONLY (luckily, there is ATM right next door)!
